content:
Analyze Your Data

Improve Recipe Performance

* Extract only the required data in input nodes.
* Minimize joins to 30 and avoid exploding joins.
* Limit transformations to 250 per recipe, and break up large recipes into smaller ones if necessary.
* Reduce multivalue columns and their width.
* Use computeExpression transformation for aggregation instead of filters.
* Avoid using compute relative for aggregation and filter nodes for conditional logic.

Simplify Editing Large Recipes

* Organize a graph with the cleanup button to improve structure and visibility.
* Speed up tasks by using keyboard shortcuts.
* Zoom in and out to change perspective.

Streamline and Improve Data Sync

* Update data with incremental sync after full syncing your data.
* Use connections to group objects for scheduling.
* Remove unused fields when syncing data to reduce performance issues.
* Don't refresh data more than necessary, and schedule associated data syncs and recipes accordingly.
* Stay within the external data sync inbound connector limit by creating views or publishing incremental data.
title: Improving Data Integration with CRM Analytics
